<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>Last updated: <strong>January 2026</strong></p>

<p>
Blessingsss ("we", "our", or "us") operates the website and mobile application 
<strong>https://blessingsss.in</strong>.
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information
when you use our application and services.
</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>

<p>We may collect the following information:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Personal information such as name, email address, phone number (if provided by the user)</li>
    <li>Device information (device model, operating system, unique identifiers)</li>
    <li>Usage data such as app interactions and features used</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>

<p>We use the collected information to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provide and maintain our services</li>
    <li>Improve app performance and user experience</li>
    <li>Communicate with users for support or updates</li>
    <li>Ensure security and prevent misuse</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>

<p>
We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties.
Your data may be shared only:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>When required by law</li>
    <li>To protect our legal rights</li>
    <li>With trusted service providers strictly for app functionality</li>
</ul>

<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>

<p>
Our app may use third-party services (such as analytics or hosting services) 
that may collect information used to identify you.
These services have their own privacy policies.
</p>

<h2>Data Security</h2>

<p>
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information.
However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.
</p>

<h2>Childrenâ€™s Privacy</h2>

